The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) says its office in Ohafia LGA in Abia State has been set ablaze Festus Okoye, the INEC spokesman, who made this known in a statement said the incident occurred on Sunday night. He, however, said there is no known cause of the fire incident yet adding that investigation into the incident is ongoing. This is coming a week after one of the commission’s offices in Essien Udim Local Government Area of Akwa Ibom state was razed DAILY Post reported that the commission in a statement confirmed that the office was set ablaze by unidentified persons in the early hours of Sunday, May 2nd, 2021. Details later… 